    "explanation": "India is basically a monsoon country. Almost all the characteristics of a monsoon climate are found here. The Himalayas make the Indian climate distinctive because they create a physical barrier for the monsoon winds, as a result of which the monsoon winds are able to spread fully over India and bring abundant rainfall. At the same time, they also protect India by blocking the cold winds coming from Central Asia.",
