    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P. R.O./A.R.O. (Pre) 2023",
    "explanation": "In India, rabi crops are cultivated mainly in north-western states such as Punjab and Haryana, although they are also cultivated in other parts of the country. Rabi crops are winter crops. In northern India, mainly north-western India, during winter, extra-tropical cyclones originating chiefly in the Mediterranean region are brought by the subtropical westerly jet streams through Türkiye, Iraq, Iran, Afghanistan, and Pakistan to north-western India, causing light winter rainfall there, which is important for rabi crops. In the Reason, tropical cyclones have been mentioned, whereas this occurs due to extra-tropical cyclones. Therefore, the Reason is incorrect. Hence, the correct answer is option (b).",
