    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P. Lower Sub. (Pre) 2013",
    "explanation": "According to the data of the UPAg portal, Government of India, in 2024–25 the highest wheat production in India was from Uttar Pradesh (30.23%). Madhya Pradesh (20.78%) and Punjab (15.26%) ranked second and third respectively. In Uttar Pradesh, the crop pattern occupying the largest area is rice–wheat. The Crown Root Initiation stage is the most critical stage for irrigation of wheat. In places where only one irrigation is possible, priority is given to irrigation at this stage, whereas in places where only two irrigations are possible, the first irrigation is given at the Crown Root Initiation stage and the second at the flowering stage. The Crown Root Initiation stage comes about 20–25 days after sowing.",
