    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 2017",
    "explanation": "The correct matching is as follows– Region Shifting Cultivation Western Ghats – Kumari South-Eastern Rajasthan – Waltare North-Eastern India – Jhum Madhya Pradesh and Chhattisgarh – Dahiya In the shifting cultivation system, tribal communities clear forests and cultivate the land. When the fertility of the land is exhausted, the same process is repeated at another location. This system is known by different names in different regions: Jhum in the hilly areas of the Northeastern states; Podu, Dabi, Koman or Bringa in Odisha; Kumari in the Western Ghats; Vatra or Waltare in South-Eastern Rajasthan; and Penda, Bewar and Dahiya in Madhya Pradesh and Chhattisgarh.",
