    "explanation": "The Earth’s axis of rotation (polar axis) is always inclined at 23½° or 23.5° to the elliptical axis. It is with the help of this tilted axis that the Earth rotates on its own axis. The Earth takes about 24 hours to complete one rotation on its axis. In the given question, the mention of the Earth’s axis of revolution is incorrect.",
    "bonus": ""
