    "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 2008",
    "explanation": "According to the question, when it is noon at Greenwich, the local time at a place is 5 p.m. This means that the time at that place is ahead of Greenwich time; therefore, that place lies to the east. The time difference is 5 hours. Therefore— 1 hour = 60 minutes 5 hours = 60 × 5 = 300 minutes 1 degree = 4 minutes ∴ 4 minutes = 1 degree 300 × 1 Therefore, 300 minutes = = 75 degrees. 4 Since this place lies to the east of the Greenwich Meridian, it is situated at 75° E.",
