    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 2006",
    "explanation": "The 360° of longitude of the Earth are divided into 24 time zones at intervals of 15° each. Thus, each time zone differs by 1 hour, and each degree of longitude corresponds to 4 minutes of time difference. Moving eastward from Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), time advances by 4 minutes at each degree of longitude, while moving westward it falls behind by 4 minutes. According to the question, the place is 3 hours ahead of Greenwich (i.e., 6 – 3 = 3 hours). The longitude for 3 hours is calculated as follows: 3 hours = 180 minutes; 180 ÷ 4 = 45° longitude. Since the time is ahead of Greenwich, the longitude will be east. Therefore, the answer is 45° East longitude.",
