    "explanation": "& (b) The midnight sun is seen north of the Arctic Circle in the Northern Hemisphere and south of the Antarctic Circle in the Southern Hemisphere. Between these circles and the poles, there are 24-hour days during summer. As a result, when it is midnight in other parts of the same hemisphere, the Sun continues to shine there locally. Since the Arctic Circle passes through the northern part of Norway, sunlight is visible there even at midnight. Therefore, Norway is called the “Land of the Midnight Sun.”",
