    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P. B.E.O. (Pre) 2019",
    "explanation": "Most of the world’s hot deserts are located on the western margins of continents between 15° and 30° north and south latitudes, such as the Sahara and Kalahari in Africa, and the Atacama in South America. In this region, trade winds blow from the north-east in the Northern Hemisphere and from the south-east in the Southern Hemisphere. By the time they reach the western side of the continents, they become dry. As a result, rainfall is negligible in these regions, which is an important factor in the formation of deserts there. Therefore, both Assertion (A) and Reason (R) are correct, and (R) is the correct explanation of (A).",
