    "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 2024",
    "explanation": "The West European type climate is found on the western margins of continents between 40° and 65° latitude in the belt of the westerlies. This climate is humid. Rainfall occurs throughout the year in every season, though it is somewhat higher in winter than in summer. The amount of rainfall varies from place to place. Generally, rainfall decreases from the coastal areas towards the interior. Note: Here, “the climate of Western Europe” has been taken in the sense of the West European type climate. However, in the literal sense, the southern part of Western Europe has an extension of the Mediterranean type of climate. In that context, option (b) would be the correct answer. The Uttar Pradesh Public Service Commission, in its preliminary answer key, considered option (a) as the correct answer for this question.",
