    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 1998",
    "explanation": "More than 60 percent of petroleum reserves are concentrated in Middle Eastern countries such as Iran, Iraq, Kuwait, and Saudi Arabia. Therefore, Statement I is correct. According to the Indian Minerals Yearbook 2022, the Middle East ranks first in crude oil reserves globally. The petroleum reserves of Texas and Alaska in the United States of America are considered nearly equivalent. Therefore, Statement II is also correct. According to the U.S. Energy Information Administration, by 2017 Texas had 1.0 billion barrels, the Gulf of Mexico had 0.8 billion barrels, and Alaska had 0.6 billion barrels of crude oil reserves. The United States of America is both a major producer and a major importer of petroleum. Therefore, Statement III is also correct. According to the 2023 data given in BGS World Mineral Production, 2019–2023, the United States of America is the world’s leading crude oil producer. The United States is an important importer of petroleum; however, it is not the largest importing country.",
