    "disputed": false,
    "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 2024",
    "explanation": "The correct matching is as follows: Planting Hearth – C.O. Sauer Cryophyte Steppe – Arctic Tundra World Floral Regions – Adolf Engler Puszta Grassland – Hungary The American geographer C.O. Sauer identified the Planting Hearth as one of the agricultural hearths, which shaped the agricultural environment through human activities and gave rise to the cultural landscape. Cryophyte Steppe denotes the vegetation of cold regions such as the Arctic Tundra. The German botanist Adolf Engler is known for his work on plant taxonomy and phytogeography. He played a pioneering role in the study of the geographical distribution of plants. He divided the floral regions of the world into four major realms. The temperate grasslands are called Puszta in the European country of Hungary.",
